snippet: Applications for unemployment benefits increased by 11,000 last week, but the jump is unlikely to cause concern about the broader health of the labor market.
abstract: Labor Dept says weekly applications for unemployment benefits rose 11,000 to seasonally adjusted 315,000, most since late June.
lead_paragraph: Applications for unemployment benefits increased by 11,000 last week, but the jump is unlikely to cause concern about the broader health of the labor market.
